## tool-read-system-prompt: read_system_prompt tool definition

### read_system_prompt(section: str = "") â†’ str
Read the system prompt or a specific section.
- No parameter / empty string: return the fully assembled system prompt.
- Integer (e.g., "0", "1", "2"): return section at that index position.
- Section name (e.g., "tools", "behavior"): return that specific section.
